The modification has been made to prevent the `toggleEditor` function from executing when the Monaco editor has `isPassThroughCode` true. The key change is adding an early return at the beginning of the function:

```typescript
if (isPassThroughCode(editorRef?.current?.getValue() ?? "")) {
  return;
}
```

This check happens before any other logic, so if the editor content is detected as pass-through code, the function will exit immediately without toggling the editor state or performing any other operations.

