messages.body:
Yes, you can handle this through `agGridProps` by setting default export options at the grid level. You would add this to your AG Grid configuration:

```typescript
agGridProps={{
  defaultCsvExportParams: {
    processCellCallback: (params) => {
      if (params.column.getColId() === "ag-Grid-AutoColumn" && params.node?.data?.order) {
        return params.node.data.order;
      }
      return params.value;
    }
  },
  defaultExcelExportParams: {
    processCellCallback: (params) => {
      if (params.column.getColId() === "ag-Grid-AutoColumn" && params.node?.data?.order) {
        return params.node.data.order;
      }
      return params.value;
    }
  }
}}
```

However, the current approach in the download component is better because:

1. **Centralized logic** - All export behavior is in one place
2. **Component-specific** - Each grid can have different export needs
3. **Reusable** - The download component can be used across different grids
4. **Flexible** - Easy to modify export options per component

The `agGridProps` approach would set it globally for that specific grid instance, but your current solution is more maintainable.

