Wait — reverting the type alone won't fix the await. Let me look at what the caller actually needs:

The caller's `setValue` is:
```ts
setValue={() => {
  helpers.setValue;  // ← bug: not invoked
}}
```

This should be:
```ts
setValue={(modelExpression) => {
  helpers.setValue(modelExpression);
}}
```

But since this is synchronous, `await setValue(...)` in handleSubmit will still work — awaiting a non-Promise just resolves immediately. So the type needs to stay as `Promise<void> | void` to be accurate, and the caller just needs the fix:

