Yes, instead of 4 separate `useField` calls just to get helpers, use `useFormikContext` to get `setFieldValue` once:

```tsx
const { setFieldValue } = useFormikContext();
```

Then replace all 4 `useField` calls and the callback with:

```tsx
const onRowSelected = useCallback(
  (event: SelectionChangedEvent<DdxField>) => {
    const selectedRecord = event.api.getSelectedNodes();
    if (selectedRecord?.length === 1) {
      const data = selectedRecord[0].data;
      helpers.setValue(data?.display_name ?? "");
      if (index != null) {
        setFieldValue(`value_${index}`, null);
        setFieldValue(`cached_value_V${index}`, null);
        setFieldValue(`cached_value_F${index}`, null);
        if (data?.data_type === "TABLE") {
          setFieldValue(`comparison_operator_${index}`, null);
        }
      }
      handleClose();
    }
  },
  [helpers, setFieldValue, index]
);
```

This is cleaner because:
- Single `setFieldValue` instead of 4 `useField` hooks
- Dependency array is minimal and correct
- No `"missing-index"` fallback strings needed since you guard with `index != null`

