Here's what the fix does:

The root cause is that `FormCustomDatePicker` sets a Formik error (via `helpers.setError`) on its field name (e.g. `value_1`). When the rows are reordered, the date picker unmounts but **Formik retains the error on that field name**. The next component that mounts with the same field name (now a numeric `FormTextField`) inherits that stale error and displays "Invalid date".

The fix adds a cleanup `useEffect` in `FormCustomDatePicker` that calls `helpers.setError(undefined)` on unmount, clearing the error from Formik before the component is replaced:

```ts
useEffect(() => {
  return () => {
    helpers.setError(undefined);
  };
  // eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/exhaustive-deps
}, []);
```

The empty dependency array ensures this only runs on unmount. The eslint disable is needed because `helpers` is intentionally excluded — we want the cleanup to capture the stable `helpers` reference from mount time, not re-register on every render.

