Good. Now I have full context. Since the URL is built on the frontend, you need 3 things: **username** (from Keycloak), **timestamp** (generated at click time), and **path** (the report path, likely a fixed value or from the row).

Looking at your active file, `textileProps?.keycloak?.token` is already used — so Keycloak is available. Here's the full solution:

---

### How `rs_path` is structured

From your example:
```
rs_path=Hrithik.Kumar@solvassolutions.com_7_59_40_PM
```
It's: `{username}_{H}_{MM}_{SS}_{AM/PM}`

---

### Full cell renderer code (in modeling-ui)

```tsx
// report-link-cell-renderer.component.tsx
import { ICellRendererParams } from "@textile/ag-grid";
import { useStaticAppContext } from "@textile/common";
import { Link } from "@textile/mui";

const REPORT_PATH = "/Apps/Reports/RunReport/ViewReport.asp";

function buildRsPath(username: string): string {
  const now = new Date();
  let hours = now.getHours();
  const minutes = now.getMinutes();
  const seconds = now.getSeconds();
  const ampm = hours >= 12 ? "PM" : "AM";
  hours = hours % 12 || 12;
  return `${username}_${hours}_${minutes}_${seconds}_${ampm}`;
}

export const ReportLinkCellRenderer = (params: ICellRendererParams) => {
  const { textileProps } = useStaticAppContext();

  const handleClick = () => {
    const token = textileProps?.keycloak?.token;
    // Keycloak JWT payload contains preferred_username or email
    const payload = token ? JSON.parse(atob(token.split(".")[1])) : {};
    const username: string = payload.preferred_username ?? payload.email ?? "unknown";

    const rsPath = buildRsPath(username);
    const reportUrl = `${REPORT_PATH}?method=SaveReport&rs_path=${rsPath}`;
    const encoded = encodeURIComponent(reportUrl);

    window.location.hash = `#/reporting?targetClassicUrlOverride=${encoded}`;
  };

  return (
    <Link component="button" variant="body2" onClick={handleClick}>
      {params.value}
    </Link>
  );
};
```

---

### How each piece is sourced

| Part | Source | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `username` | Keycloak JWT `preferred_username` / `email` | `Hrithik.Kumar@solvassolutions.com` |
| timestamp | `new Date()` at click time | `7_59_40_PM` |
| `REPORT_PATH` | hardcoded (fixed classic path) | `/Apps/Reports/RunReport/ViewReport.asp` |
| base URL | fetched by `IFrameContainer` from BFF | `https://am-wilmington-biz...` |

The `IFrameContainer` handles the base URL automatically — you only set the hash with the relative path override.

---

### One thing to confirm

Does `rs_path` need to match an **existing saved report** on the server (i.e. it's a report identifier stored somewhere), or is it generated fresh each time the user clicks? If it's a stored identifier, it would need to come from the row data instead of being generated from the current timestamp.
